cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM 

The paper presents a model based on spatiotemporal summary statistics computed from a CNN trained on object recognition. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of CNNs for feature extraction and prediction suggests that the paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also deals with motion prediction, which suggests that it may belong to the graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
